Bee

Fumble, fumble,
heap the honeyed wax,
where the sun has shined
you will find your goal.
Upon the fluted violets
you hum and buzz,
that bliss has brought.
The scent is sweet,
gather by the hour's mark
and glory in the sunshine.

— H.D.

- HD
